  "tldr": [
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/ai",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Investigating idiosyncrasies in AI fiction",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.03136",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/hjuopb",
      "score": 4,
      "comments": 2,
      "author": "kehn",
      "published": "2026-07-02T12:02:29Z",
      "bullets": [
        "LLM-generated fiction exhibits distinct linguistic fingerprints, overusing specific transition phrases and vocabulary like \"delve\" due to RLHF alignment.",
        "Instruction-tuned models like GPT-4 and Claude show predictable narrative structures, sanitized themes, and repetitive character development archetypes.",
        "Developers mitigate these stylistic tells by adjusting temperature, top-p sampling parameters, or fine-tuning on diverse, human-authored creative datasets."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "If you’re a button, you have one job",
      "url": "https://unsung.aresluna.org/if-youre-a-button-you-have-one-job/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/zhizsf",
      "score": 2,
      "comments": 1,
      "author": "noncrab",
      "published": "2026-07-05T08:24:06Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Use semantic HTML `<button>` elements rather than `<div>` to gain native keyboard navigation, focus management, and screen reader support automatically.",
        "Custom components require explicit `role=\"button\"`, `tabindex=\"0\"`, and keydown event handlers for Space and Enter keys to satisfy WCAG standards.",
        "Use `<a>` strictly for URL-based navigation, reserving `<button>` elements for triggering in-page actions, form submissions, and state changes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Bad Epoll (CVE-2026-46242)",
      "url": "https://github.com/J-jaeyoung/bad-epoll",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/drf6my",
      "score": 28,
      "comments": 6,
      "author": "dzwdz",
      "published": "2026-07-04T18:40:12Z",
      "bullets": [
        "CVE-2026-46242 is a newly disclosed vulnerability in the Linux kernel epoll I/O event notification subsystem.",
        "The vulnerability poses risks of local privilege escalation (LPE) and potential container escapes via memory corruption or race conditions.",
        "Systems administrators should monitor upstream Linux kernel patches and restrict unprivileged user namespaces to mitigate exploitation vectors."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "I Don't Maintain My Homelab",
